Gets the nearest stations (and its loading-points) from the given location which match the given filters.
The required parameters are 'latitude' and 'longitude', the optional parameters are the loading-points' minimum-energy-in-kW (badly named as 'capacity') and the loading-points' connector-types (badly named as 'types').

Gets the stations (and its loading-points) which match all of the given filters.
(The filter latitude only works in combination with the filter longitude and vice versa.
The filter maxDistanceInKm only works in combination with the filters latitude and longitude.)
The multi-character-wildcard '%' may be used within the text fields 'label', 'description', 'postCode', 'city', 'street' and 'evseId'.
If not using a wildcard the text fields 'label', 'description', 'city' and 'street' will use a fuzzy search which accepts small variations or errors (f.e. looking for 'wein' will get you 'Wien').
For pagination you may use 'fromIndex' and 'maxResults'. In any case no more than 1,000 results will be returned.
